    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Rockbridge County was formed in 1778 from Augusta and Botetourt Counties.  An additional part of Botetourt County was added in 1785.    
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Rockbridge County (Va.) Slave Patrol Appointment, May 7, 1861. Consists of a document appointing William Allison, Joseph Saville, and William S. Newcomer to patrol at least once a week "all negro quarters" and other places suspected of harboring "unlawful assemblages of slaves as may stroll from one plantation to another."     
</p>
    </scopecontent>
